title: Grateful Dead Live at Capitol Centre on 1991-03-17
lineage: Dat (Sony R500)> Behringer UltraMatch SRC2000> SEK'D Prodif Plus> Samplitude v7.02 Professional> SHN; Recorded By Jeff Metchik (sp?); Transferred By Charlie Miller
description: Hell In A Bucket, Sugaree, Walkin' Blues, El Paso, Queen Jane Approximately, Rubin & Cherise, Let It Grow China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Women Are Smarter, Crazy Fingers-> Truckin'-> New Speedway Boogie-> Drums-> Jam-> The Wheel-> All Along The Watchtower-> Black Peter-> Around & Around, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: poor sound Great setlist, muffled sounding recording though.  Four stars for show, two for recording.

first day of the rest of my life although my first show was in 86, I only saw a handful between then and this tour, when I 'left home' to live on tour...
melancholy...
Ruby was a great welcoming to the next four years...

actually VG recording This is actually a very good FOB. Be patient and use a little EQ. Early in set 1 there is a LOUD clapper and some talking but these fade away and this turns into a very nice sounding recording. 

The show is wonderful, dripping with desire and adventure.

Reuben!! I was at this show, and all Landover/DC shows from ‘89 to ‘95. I felt like the Dead played special treats for the Terrapins down the road at College Park. This show didn’t disappoint; how could it? The only Reuben and Cherise ever played by the band and a killer New Speedway Boogie. Really good time had!
